    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">What's the difference between Prosecco DOCG and DOC quality levels?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">Prosecco DOCG represents the highest quality tier, produced exclusively in the historic Conegliano-Valdobbiadene and Asolo zones using stricter regulations and lower yields. DOC Prosecco covers a much larger area across nine provinces and allows higher production volumes, resulting in generally lighter, more accessible wines. DOCG bottles typically cost $18-40 while DOC versions range from $8-20, with DOCG offering more complexity and aging potential.</p>
